ENTRY            A1397   20260219   20260508   20260508       A133
SUBENT        A1397001   20260219   20260508   20260508       A133
BIB                 11         29
TITLE      Structure of 7Be.
            (I) The 6Li(p,p')6Li* reaction
AUTHOR     (W.D.Harrison)
REFERENCE  (J,NP/A,92,253,1967)
           (T,HARRISON,1966) - Tables; technical details
REL-REF    (O,C1003001,W.D.Harrison+,J,PR,132,2607,1963) - Elastic
           scattering of protons by Li6 (same data in Table 1 of
           thesis)
           (O,A1230001,W.D.Harrison+,J,NP/A,92,260,1967) -
            (II) The 6Li(p,p")6Li** and 4He(3He,p")6Li** reactions
INSTITUTE  (1USACAL)
FACILITY   (VDGT,1USACAL) ONR-CIT
SAMPLE     (3-LI-6,ENR=0.99) Targets of 6Li (isotopic abundance
           99%) with the thickness from 70 to 300 ug/cm2 were
           evaporated in situ on 500 Angstr. thick nickel foils.
           These were mounted over 7.9-mm diameter holes punched
           in 0.18-mm thick tantalum.
DETECTOR   (SIBAR) Two silicon surface-barrier detectors, each
           with a resolution of about 40 to 50 keV, were used.
           One at a fixed angle as a target monitor.
MONITOR    (3-LI-6(P,EL)3-LI-6,,DA)
MONIT-REF  (C1003001,W.D.Harrison+,J,PR,132,2607,1963)
HISTORY    (19820507C) Compilation produced by Arzamas RFNC-VNIIEF
           (19990317U)CNPD: corrected 4-dig. year and lower cases.
           (20250916A) SD: Corrections in all Subents.
           (20260219A) SD: The digitized data were replaced with
           tabulated data from thesis. Corrections in all Subents.
           SF3=INL -> EL; SF5=PAR deleted from MONITOR reaction in
           Subent 001.
ENDBIB              29
NOCOMMON             0          0
ENDSUBENT           32
SUBENT        A1397002   20260219   20260508   20260508       A133
BIB                  4         12
REACTION   (3-LI-6(P,INL)3-LI-6,PAR,DA)
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-1) The standard error in the normalization
           (ERR-2) Systematic errors caused by geometrical
           inaccuracies in the scattering chamber, and in some
           cases, by relative normalization errors in data taken
           with different targets.
STATUS     (TABLE,,W.D.Harrison,T,HARRISON,1967) Table 2 (part
           of data presented on fig.2 of NP/A,92,253,1967)
HISTORY    (20250916A) SD: SF9=EXP deleted from REACTION code.
           STATUS updated. COS-ERR->COS-ERR-D.
           (20260219A) SD: BIB updated. The digitized data were
           replaced with tabulated data from thesis.
ENDBIB              12
COMMON               1          3
E-LVL
MEV
      2.184
ENDCOMMON            3
